# Forgejo automated operations — example crontab
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# INSTALL
#   crontab < crontab.example          # replaces your existing crontab
#   crontab -e                         # or open the editor and paste/merge
#
# PREREQUISITES — run once before enabling the cron jobs:
#   mkdir -p /var/backups/forgejo      # backup archive destination
#   chmod 700 /var/backups/forgejo     # restrict: archives contain all repo data
#   mkdir -p /var/log/forgejo          # cron appends stdout+stderr here
#
# ALL TIMES ARE UTC.  The instance is provisioned in ewr (New Jersey);
# 02:00–06:00 UTC is overnight US-East, a good low-traffic window.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Environment ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# cron starts with a nearly empty environment.  Spell out everything the
# scripts depend on so they behave identically to an interactive shell run.

SHELL=/bin/bash

# Extend PATH to wherever terraform, vault, docker, zstd, and ykman live.
# Run 'echo $PATH' in your normal login shell and paste the result here.
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/snap/bin

# Set HOME so that ~/.ssh/id_ed25519 (admin SSH key) and ~/.vault.token
# resolve correctly.  Replace with your actual home directory.
HOME=/home/dhorn

# Suppress the per-job email cron normally sends on any stdout/stderr output;
# we redirect each job to a dedicated log file instead.
# Change to a real address to get email on failure: MAILTO=you@example.com
MAILTO=""

# ── Twice-daily repository export ────────────────────────────────────────────
# 03:00 and 15:00 UTC every day.
#
# Exports every Forgejo repository (including wikis) to a timestamped
# zstd-compressed tar archive of bare git bundles.  Each bundle is a complete
# clone; restore with:
#   tar -xf forgejo-YYYYMMDD-HHMM.tar.zst
#   git clone path/to/<owner>/<repo>.bundle  destination/
#
# Auto-detection: export-git.sh reads .last-provider to find the right
# Terraform directory, retrieves the IP from 'terraform output', then SSHes
# as deploy@ to generate a short-lived admin token — no credentials to embed.
#
# Archive rotation: daily-export.sh keeps the 14 most recent archives
# (7 days at twice-daily cadence) and deletes older ones automatically.
# Adjust KEEP= inside cron/daily-export.sh to change the retention window.
#
# Note: the % character is special in crontab (treated as newline); that is
# why the date format string lives inside the helper script, not inline here.
0 3,15 * * *  /home/dhorn/git-deploy/cron/daily-export.sh \
              >> /var/log/forgejo/export.log 2>&1

# ── Weekly rolling instance rotation ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 02:00 UTC every Sunday.
#
# Provisions a fresh cloud instance, mirrors all repos updated in the past
# 7 days, verifies the new instance is healthy, then destroys the old instance.
# The old instance is only destroyed if verification passes — on any failure
# the old instance stays up untouched and the error is logged.
#
# Why rotate weekly?
#   • Let's Encrypt short-lived IP certs expire in 160 hours (~6.7 days).
#     Weekly rotation ensures the certbot renewal path is exercised regularly
#     rather than discovered broken under pressure.
#   • Forces the full provision + deploy pipeline to run on a schedule,
#     surfacing Terraform drift, image changes, or cloud-API breakage before
#     they become an emergency.
#   • Achieves automatic credential rotation: every week brings a fresh TLS
#     certificate and a new SSH host key.
#
# ROTATE_PROVIDER / ROTATE_REGION / ROTATE_PLAN are read by the script as
# environment variables.  Inline them here to override per-job without editing
# the script.  Match them to your current provider's available plans/regions.
#
# See cron/weekly-rotate.sh for the full workflow and failure-handling details.
0 2 * * 0     ROTATE_PROVIDER=vultr \
              ROTATE_REGION=ewr \
              ROTATE_PLAN=vc2-1c-0.5gb \
              /home/dhorn/git-deploy/cron/weekly-rotate.sh \
              >> /var/log/forgejo/migrate.log 2>&1
